<HEAD><TITLE>METEO-FRANCE : Today's weather</TITLE></HEAD> 
 
<BODY> 
<H1><CENTER>M&eacute;t&eacute;o-France weather report<HR SIZE=5></CENTER></H1>
<center>
<H3><a href="/meteo/conditions.html">Usage rights of M&eacute;t&eacute;o-France images</a></H3>
<h3><a href="#infop"><i>About this page...</i></a></h3>
</center>

<H2>Meteorological satellites</H2>
To make a forecast, numeric models and forecasters needs to know an initial state of the atmosphere. This state is defined with observations of the atmosphere. <b>The meteorological satellites</b>  contribute to <b>the real time observation,</b> such as ground observations, vertical reading by sounding balloon, etc...
<P>
Geostationnary satellites, located 36 000 km above the equator, take part in global meteorological monitoring. The European satellite, METEOSAT-5, is at longitude 0.
<P>
<h3> Latest METEOSAT's images :</h3>
These images are updated 30 minutes after observation hour. Hours are given in <a href="#UTC">U.T.C.</a>
<P>
