<H2><i><a name="infop">Useful information</a></i></H2>
<UL TYPE=SQUARE>
<LI> <a name="UTC"></a><b>U.T.C.</b> : Universal Time Coordinates, equivalent to
 G.M.T. (Greenwich Mean Time). In France, summer time is 2 hours earlier than U.
 T.C., winter time is 1 hour earlier than U.T.C.<BR>

<i>Ex : On 15 May 95, METEOSAT image at 06h00 U.T.C. was made at 08h, it was on this page at 8h30 (official time).</i>
<P>
<LI> Images and forecast text are reachable with constant links, allowing you to get the latest version. But, if you can not get the lastest data because of a too large disk cache,  you can use these dated links :
