<TITLE> IPM - Integrated Parallel Macros </TITLE>
<H1> <IMG SRC="../Images/logoipm.gif"> IPM</H1>

<HR>
<H2>IPM in a few words:</H2>

IPM is not a new message passing library. Not even a library. It is 
just a package of m4 macros built on top of existing message passing
libraries such as PVM 3.2.x, 3.3.x or PARMACS 6.0. It allows the user
to choose between parallel libraries at compilation time although he
retains a single source code - it therefore reduces development costs
while permitting the use of libraries that may be better suited for a
particular hardware configuration.  New releases of these libraries are
hidden from the user because of the compact IPM interface.
IPM has been designed keeping in mind the specifications for MPI.
An MPI subset, built on top of IPM calls, is provided with the IPM package.
<HR>

<H2>More about IPM:</H2>

<UL>
  <LI><A HREF="../Latex/TR_PA_95_01.ps">
    <B>IPM 2.3 User's Guide and Reference Manual (ps)</B></A>
</UL>
<HR>

<H2>Obtaining IPM</H2>

The IPM package is available by anonymous ftp from orion.cerfacs.fr
(138.63.200.33) in a compressed format <i>ipm2.3.tar.Z"</i>. After an
<i> uncompress </i> and a <i> tar xvf ipm2.3.tar </i> you can retrieve
the following directory:
<PRE>
  ipm/    
          - Readme
          - doc/
                    - ipmdoc.ps
          - example/
	            - gridsum/
                    - ring/
          - include/
                    - <A HREF="./v23_ipm.h.pm6">ipm.h.pm6</A>
                    - <A HREF="./v23_ipm.h.pvm">ipm.h.pvm</A>
          - mpi/
                    - Readme
                    - makefile
                    - mpif.h
                    - mpiipm.F
</PRE>
<HR>

<H2>Current Status</H2>
The IPM 3.0 is currently in progress. It will contain:
<UL>
  <LI> MPI and P4 interfaces (already done)
  <LI> A void interface!
  <LI> A PVM-T3D interface.
  <LI> A library version of m4 macros
  <LI> A more extended documentation
  <LI> you can download the current state of the art include files:
    <UL>
      <LI> <A HREF="./v30_ipm.h.mpi">ipm.h.mpi</A>
      <LI> <A HREF="./v30_ipm.h.pm6">ipm.h.pm6</A>
      <LI> <A HREF="./v30_ipm.h.pvm">ipm.h.pvm</A>
      <LI> <A HREF="./v30_ipm.h.p4">ipm.h.p4</A>
    </UL>
</UL>

<HR>

<H2>IPM Mailing List</H2>
If you wish to receive up to date informations on IPM, you can suscribe to the
IPM mailing list by sending a mail to one of the contacts:

<HR>

<H2>Contacts:</H2>
<UL>
<LI><B><A HREF="mailto:Luc.Giraud@cerfacs.fr">Luc Giraud</A> ( CERFACS )</B>
<LI><B><A HREF="mailto:Eric.Sevault@meteo.fr">Eric Sevault</A> ( METEO-FRANCE)</B>
<LI><B><A HREF="mailto:kemenade@imhfhp1.epfl.ch">Vincent Van Kemenade</A> (E.P.F.L.)</B>
</UL>

<HR>
