<PRE>
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_add"> >  Script cc_add </A>
 >  -------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  Create a file or a directory in current view.
 >  -------    Warning: you must be in the rigth directory
 >               for creating the new element.
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_add -f filename [-i import-file] | -d directory
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  -f = filename to create
 >  ----------    -i = import file for the new file
 >                -d = directory to create
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_cat"> >  Script cc_cat </A>
 >  -------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  cat a arbitrary directory or file from an other branch
 >  -------    or release
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_cat [-f filename | -d directory] [-u user] [-r release]
 >  -----           [-b branch]
 >
 >  Parameters :  -f = filename to cat
 >  ----------    -d = directory (display contents)
 >                -u = user logname
 >                -r = release label (without -u or -b option indicates
 >                     the main version of this release)
 >                -b = branch name extension
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_config"> >  Script cc_config </A>
 >  ----------------
 >
 >  Purpose :   display default configuration informations:
 >  -------     "project release global-path hostname"
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_config [-p project] [-l]
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  -p = project name
 >  ----------    -l = long format output
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_copy"> >  Script cc_copy </A>
 >  --------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  Copy a set of files from a clearcase database
 >  -------    with the same unix architecture.
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_copy -l list | -v | -b -d outdir
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  -l = file with the list of files to extract
 >  ----------    -v = copy the entire view
 >                -b = copy the current branch
 >                -d = output directory
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_diff"> >  Script cc_diff </A>
 >  --------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  Diplays differences between multiple versions files
 >  -------    (predecessor by default). The output is displayed
 >             either as a sequential format (-x), or a separate 
 >             X window (-w) or graphical interface (default)
 >             The current version is not selected by default.
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_diff -f filename | -d directory | -l list [-h] [-w] [-x]
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  -f = file name
 >  ----------    -d = directory name
 >                -h = choose in history of the file
 >                -l = arbitary list of (possibly external) elements 
 >                     with the following format:
 >                       element-name RELEASE
 >                       element-name [user_RELEASE_branch[/version]]
 >                -w = use a separate X window for results
 >                -x = disable X interfaces (for vt100 like screens)
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_dir"> >  Script cc_dir </A>
 >  -------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  Return unix directory of the specified file
 >  -------    as well as associated project and release if
 >             directory found in global tables otherwise
 >             returns only directory and project in the current view [-v]
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_dir -f filename [-p project] [-r release] [-v]
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  -f = filename
 >  ----------    -p = project name
 >                -r = release label (useless if -v is active)
 >                -v = flag to check in the current view
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_edit"> >  Script cc_edit </A>
 >  --------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  Check out a element file for editing or modifications
 >  -------    and replace it in the database unless -k is specified
 >             A warning is displayed if modified versions of the
 >             file exist for the same release.
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_edit -f filename [-k] [-q]
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  -f = file name to check out
 >  ----------    -k = keep the file checked out
 >                -q = quiet mode: do not display the list of other
 >                     modifications. Usefull in non-interactive mode.
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_expand"> >  Script cc_expand </A>
 >  ----------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  expand a single file xor
 >  -------           a list of files xor
 >                    the branch matching to the current view
 >                    including dependencies ( for modified .h files) xor
 >                    the complete view.
 >
 >  Usage : cc_expand -f file | -l list | -b branch [-o] | -a | -v 
 >                    -c ccpout | -s srcout | -d dirout [-e ccpdef] [-t]
 >
 >  Parameters :  -f = single file to expand
 >  ----------    -l = filename with list of file to expand
 >                -o = flag for expending dependencies in other projects
 >                     used only with -b
 >                -b = branch name extension matching to the current view,
 >                     with potential primary branches
 >                -a = all branch defined in the view selection rules
 >                -v = flag for expanding all the current view
 >                -c = file to receive cpp outputs
 >                -s = file to receive source concatenation
 >                -d = directory to receive cpp single files output
 >                -e = comma-separated list of cpp define options
 >                -t = tar and gzip the cpp dir output (-d only)
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_getview"> >  Script cc_getview </A>
 >  -----------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  Get an existing view (interactive mode or not)
 >  -------    or create one (interactive mode)
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_getview [-p project] [-r release | "all" ] [-b branch]
 >  -----               [-j job] [-u user]
 >
 >  Parameters :  -p = project name
 >  ----------    -r = release label | "all" for all releases
 >                -b = branch name extension, and potential primary branches
 >                -j = job to execute in a non-interactive session
 >                -u = disable user logname selection and therefore
 >                     select user specified views (including public views)
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_help"> >  Script cc_help </A>
 >  --------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  Retrieve on-line documentation or post an SOS
 >  -------    to the VOB administrator
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_help [-c command]
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  -c = command ( script name )
 >  ----------   
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_init"> >  Script cc_init </A>
 >  --------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  Initiate user's configuration for ClearCase
 >  -------
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_init [-p project]
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  -p = main project
 >  ----------   
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_klviews"> >  Script cc_klviews </A>
 >  -----------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  Kill users's view_server processes
 >  -------
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_klviews
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  none
 >  ----------
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_list"> >  Script cc_list </A>
 >  --------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  List all elements of a branch in current directory
 >  ------- 
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_list [-b branch] [-r release] [-u user] [-o]
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  -b = branch name extension and primary branches
 >  ----------         default = first selected branch of the current view
 >                -r = release label
 >                -u = user login name
 >                -o = formatted output
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_log"> >  Script cc_log </A>
 >  -------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  write user's cc scripts logfile
 >  -------
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_log command-line
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  command-line = calling sequence of the cc script
 >  ----------
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_ls"> >  Script cc_ls </A>
 >  ------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  To perform a documented ls operation
 >  -------
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_ls [-r | -d] [-vob] [elements]
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  -r = recursive list
 >  ----------    -d = list directory itself not its contents
 >                -vob = list only elements of the current vob
 >                elements = elements to list
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_merge"> >  Script cc_merge </A>
 >  ---------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  Merge specified file or branch to the current view.
 >  -------    The "from" version is defined by the release, user logname
 >             and optional branch name extension.
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_merge [-f filename | -d directory | -l list] 
 >  -----             [-r release] [-b branch] [-u user] [-v view-tag]
 >                    -m mode [-x]
 >
 >  Parameters :  -f = file name to merge (the whole branch if not supplied)
 >  ----------    -d = directory to merge (the directory itself, not the
 >                     contents) - set to all for merging all the matching
 >                     directories
 >                -l = filename including list of elements to merge
 >                -r = release label
 >                -b = branch name extension
 >                -u = user logname
 >                -v = remote view-tag to merge
 >                -m = working mode (no default): 
 >                       print: display merges but do not perform, 
 >                       auto : perform merges in automatic mode (with abort),
 >                       step : perform merges but ask for any change
 >                -x = disable X interfaces (for vt100 like screens)
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_mod"> >  Script cc_mod </A>
 >  -------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  Returns historic list of modifications performed on the
 >  -------    specified file for a given release.
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_mod -f filename | - d directory [-r release]
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  -f = filename
 >  ----------    -d = directory name
 >                -r = release label
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_popul"> >  Script cc_popul </A>
 >  ---------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  Populate the default project with contents of a directory.
 >  -------    Do not create new elements.
 >             Put modified elements in the current view according
 >               to directory location returned by cc_dir.
 >             The source directory could contain files wich do not
 >               belong to the project. These files are copied to
 >               $HOME/ccase/tmp/nf_$directory/ for a further
 >               use (with cc_add for example).
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_popul -d directory
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  -d = source directory
 >  ----------   
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_popvob"> >  Script cc_popvob </A>
 >  ----------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  Populate a VOB with data from the current directory
 >  -------
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_popvob -p project
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  -p = project name (vob-tag) of the VOB to populate
 >  ----------
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_public"> >  Script cc_public </A>
 >  ----------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  Create a public view matching to the current view.
 >  -------    The name of the public view is :
 >             project_public_RELEASE_[LOGNAME || branch]
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_public [-b branch]
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  -b = branch name extension. If not supplied, the user
 >  ----------         logname is taken as the branch name extension
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_put"> >  Script cc_put </A>
 >  -------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  Check in a file or directory previously checked out.
 >  -------    If the element hadn't been modified, uncheckout it.
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_put -f filename | -d directory
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  -f = filename to check in
 >  ----------    -d = directory name to check in
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_quit"> >  Script cc_quit </A>
 >  --------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  Quit the current view
 >  -------
 >
 >  Usage :  . cc_quit
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  None... but be aware of the point before the command
 >  ----------   
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_rmbranch"> >  Script cc_rmbranch </A>
 >  ------------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  Remove data belonging to the view's branch
 >  -------    Do not remove the branch type (unless -t) or the view
 >             so the current view and branch creation mechanism
 >             are still valid.
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_rmbranch [-f filename | -d dirname] [-q] [-t]
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  -f = branch-file to remove
 >  ----------    -d = directory-branch to remove
 >                -q = quiet mode (supress confirmation step)
 >                -t = also remove the branch type itself, so that
 >                     no more modification/creation is possible
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_rmlast"> >  Script cc_rmlast </A>
 >  ----------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  Remove last version of a file or directory
 >  -------    in the current view
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_rmlast -f filename | -d directory
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  -f = filename
 >  ----------    -d = directory name
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_rmview"> >  Script cc_rmview </A>
 >  ----------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  Remove a user's view
 >  -------
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_rmview [-p project] [-r release | "all"]
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  -p = project name
 >  ----------    -r = release label | "all" for all releases
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_update"> >  Script cc_update </A>
 >  ----------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  Update releases and paths informations of the
 >  -------    Clear Case config file
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_update [-p project] [-r release]
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  -p = project name
 >  ----------    -r = release label
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_versions"> >  Script cc_versions </A>
 >  ------------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  return list of :
 >  -------     - available releases for a given project (default)
 >              - releases and branches with active views (option -b)
 >              - branches for a given release (option -r [release])
 >              - all branches for all users (option -a)
 >              - all branches for an given user (option -a -u [user])
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_versions [-r release] [-a] [-b] [-p project] [-u logname]
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  -p = project name 
 >  ----------    -r = release name
 >                -b = option for listing branches
 >                -u = user logname
 >                -a = flag for all branches
 >
<HR size=10><A NAME="cc_view"> >  Script cc_view </A>
 >  --------------
 >
 >  Purpose :  Return informations about a view:
 >  -------    view-name project-path and selection rules
 >
 >  Usage :  cc_view [-s] [-t viewtag] [-e]
 >  -----
 >
 >  Parameters :  -s = short display (view name)
 >  ----------    -t = view tag
 >                -e = edit option, "subcommand num-rule arg1 [arg2]":
 >                     r  : add the release (no check out)
 >                     b  : add the branch (no check out)
 >                     bb : add the branch (mkbranch current)
 >                     br : add branch and release (mkbranch)
 >                     bw : add branch with mkbranch on the 2nd 
 >                          specified branch
 >                     d  : delete rules
 >                     u  : undo - exit without any change
 >                     ok : exit and save changes
 >
</PRE>
<HR size=10>
