<HEAD>
<TITLE>THE METEOPOLE</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<HR><P>
<H1>THE "METEOPOLE"</H1>
<HR><P>


<IMG align=middle BORDER=8 SRC="http://www.meteo.fr/meteopol/images/mtopole.gif">

</CENTER>
<DT>

<UL>

Toulouse is the French Capital city of Meteorology : in 1991, all National Research and Operational Services, the "Haute-Garonne" Meteorological district Centre, as well as the International Conference centre of M&eacute;t&eacute;o-France, were finally brought together on the site where ENM has been since 1982, thus creating one of the most important meteorological complexes in the world (with about 1000 Meteorologists) : the Toulouse M&eacute;t&eacute;opole, in which various other bodies cooperating with M&eacute;t&eacute;o-France (such as the Cerfacs : European Centre for Research and Formation in Scientific Advanced Calculations, or the environmental Navy Unit) are also located.<P>

In such a scientific and technical environment, taking into account the collaboration of ENM with the Toulouse Paul Sabatier University (which also has activities in the atmospheric field) and with other GE located in Toulouse, the teaching of meteorology benefits from a true synergy in almost all its aspects.<P>

<HR>

</BODY>
</DOC>
