<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> SYMPOSIUM SUR LES LOGICIELS DE GESTION DE DONNEES</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<CENTER>
<HR SIZE=6>
<H2>SYMPOSIUM ON MASS STORAGE PRODUCTS </H2>
</CENTER>
<HR SIZE=6>
<HR>
<DL>
<DT>
This first part of the conference should begin on Tueday, November 12 at 09.00,
and end at 12.30 on Wednesday, November 13.
<HR>
</UL>
<B> PRESENTATION OF COMPETITIVE HSM SOFTWARE TECHNOLOGY</B></UL>
Several current UniTree sites are preparing for major compute
service upgrades which will severely impact the data service
requirements.</UL>
To aid in orientation about currently (or shortly) avalaible technology,
the major HSM products running on Unix-like operating systems will be
presented.</UL>
It is planned to have both a vendor and, if possible, also user presentations
for all products covered. Currently, this product list includes : </UL>
<PRE>
<LI> ADSM, Turbo/ADSM           IBM Storage Systems</LI>
<LI> AMASS/DataMgr              EMASS </LI>
<LI> DMF                        Cray Research/SGI</LI>
<LI> HPSS                       IBM Government Systems</LI>
<LI> SAM-FS                     Large Storage Components</LI>
<LI> UniTree                    Unitree Inc., HP/Convex, Ahmdahl</LI>
</PRE>
</UL>
This list of products is not closed, we are soliciting other
proposals.</UL>
</UL>
<B> PRESENTATION OF HIGH-PERFORMANCE HARDWARE TECHNOLOGY</B></UL>
Several high-performance devices will be presented by their vendors. The status 
and future of each product will be detailed. The covered product should be : </UL>
<PRE>
<LI> D2		       Ampex</LI>
<LI> D3/Redwood            Storagetek </LI>
<LI> 3590/Magstar          IBM</LI>
</PRE>
</UL>
<HR>
</BODY>

</HTML>
