<HEAD>
<TITLE> 8TH UTUG </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<CENTER>
<DT>
<HR SIZE=6>
<H3><blink> -- LOCAL ARRANGEMENTS -- </blink></H3>

</CENTER>
<HR SIZE=6>

<HR>
Both parts of this meeting should last 1.5 day (Data management symposium
from Monday 12 at 9.00 until Wednesday 13 at 12.30 ; UTUG meeting from
Wednesday 13 at 14.00 until Thursday 14 at 18.030).</UL>

During the conference, all the talks will be given in English.</UL>

The meeting (except the very last Unitree business session) is <B>
OPENED TO ANYONE INTERESTED IN THE MATTER, WHATEVER PEOPLE ARE FAMILIAR
WITH UNITREE OR NOT.</B>. Thus, especially the first part of the meeting
(HSM Symposium) should put together different users and vendors involved
in data management problems. </UL>

There is no registration fee.</UL>

A more detailed program is now <a href="../program.html">available.</a></UL>

<LI>
You may ask for a registration form for this meeting, 
<A HREF="mailto:utug96@meteo.fr"> by sending </a>
a message with your name, quality and company.</LI></UL>

<LI>
You may send remarks or suggestions for this conference,
<A HREF="mailto:utug-officer@dkrz.de"> by sending </a>
an e-mail to the organisation comittee.</UL> </LI>
</UL>
<HR>

You may announce this meeting to anybody who might be interested
in the subject.</UL>

The way to reach "Meteopole" is available <a href="reach_us.html">here.</a> </UL>
<HR>
<H3> -- Organisation committee -- </H3>

<LI>   Ellen SALMON, NASA Goddard, USA, UNITREE users' group president</LI>
<LI>   Hartmut FICHTEL, DKRZ, ALLEMAGNE</LI>
<LI>   Betty Jo ARMSTEAD, NASA Lewis, USA</LI>
<LI>   Joe LOPEZ, San Diego Supercomputing Center, USA </LI>
<LI>   Alain BEURAUD, Meteo-France, FRANCE.</LI>
</UL>
<HR>
