<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>AVISO : Archive, Preview, Interpretation of data of Oceanographic Satellites</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY><P>
<H1><CENTER>AVISO : Archive, Preview, Interpretation of data of Oceanographic Satellites</CENTER></H1>
<HR SIZE=5>
<P>
<P>
The initial idea of AVISO vent-flux system (AVF) is the consequence of an inquiry in 1987 among principal french scientific laboratories involved in research program about meteorology, oceanography and remote detection. These expressed a significant requirement about parameters and products for the study of ocean-atmosphere interface, stem at once from digital models of weather forecast and oceanographic satellites.<P>

<H4>Since 1987, this requirement have grown again for the following reasons :</H4>

<UL>
<LI>The recent oceanographic satellites (ERS, TOPEX/POSEIDON...), taking for the most new instruments, require an important amount of data of quality, as well as high performance tools for purposes of calibrating and authentication.<P>

<LI>Constants progress of digital weather forecast systems have significantly increased the quality, and so the use of products which are stemed from.<P>

</UL>

To reply to these requirements, M&eacute;t&eacute;o-France has taken charge since 1983 of development of AVF, including following functions :<P>

<H2>ARCHIVE</H2> 

AVF archive fields about ocean-atmosphere interface stemed from digital models of weather forecast and sea condition forecast of M&eacute;t&eacute;o-France and ECMWF (European Center of Meteorological Weather Forecast). AVF archive also real-time data of satellites ERS, wind and wave data of satellite TOPEX/POSEIDON, as well as products like surface sea temperature and incident solar flux developped at Centre de M&eacute;t&eacute;orologie Spatiale at Lannion from meteorological satellites NOAA and M&eacute;t&eacute;osat. Finally, AVF archive meteorological observations of ships and buoies conveyed on worldwide meteorological network.<P>

<H2>PROCESSING</H2>
 
To reply in a efficient and progressive way to expressed requirements, AVF propose also products stemed from some processing :<P>

<UL>
<LI>Systematic processing : these processing have like principal aim the follow-up of feed and quality of the archive, and include a data quality control, as well as <A HREF="prodbilan_eng.html">statistical and graphic products `QUICK-LOOK'</A>, et <A HREF="prodcoll_eng.html">colocation</A> of satellites and conventiona `QUIasurements.<P>

<LI>Processing by request : many data of archive processing could be made by request, about for example calculation of derived statistical or geophysical parameters, or re-analysis of fields arranging differents media sources.<P>
</UL>

<H2>PLACING DATA AT DISPOSAL</H2>

Placing data at disposal is proposing by differents means (network, DAT etc...), according to user's requirements and the mass of concerned data. Besides, AVF proposes direct access by server to <A HREF="catalogue_eng.html">catalogue of available data</A>.<P>
<HR>
<A HREF="index_eng.html"><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE WIDTH=115 HEIGHT=25 HSPACE=5 SRC="images/aviso2.gif">Back to AVISO Home Page</A>
