<HEAD>
<TITLE>Conventional observations</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY>
<H1><CENTER>Conventional observations</CENTER></H1>
<HR SIZE=5> 
<BR>

Data are collected at METEO-FRANCE by way of worldwide network of transmission.<P>

The archive begins in July 1991, and will be timelessness on living time of system.<P>

Cover is global. <P>

<H2>Surface conventional observations</H2>

<B>Parameters :</B><P>

<UL>
<LI>wind,
<LI>pressure,
<LI>trend,
<LI>temperatures,
<LI>nebulousness,
<LI>clouds,
<LI>the present,
<LI>Sea state,
<LI>ice.
</UL>
<BR>

<H2>Conventional observations by radiosonde explorations</H2>

Profiles of surface geopotentials, temperatures, humidity up to an altitude of 25 km.<P>

<HR>
<A HREF="index_eng.html"><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE WIDTH=115 HEIGHT=25 HSPACE=5 SRC="images/aviso2.gif">Back to AVISO Home Page</A>
