<HEAD>
<TITLE>Satellites observations</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1><CENTER>Satellites observations</CENTER></H1>
<HR SIZE=5> 
<BR>
In order to valorize and to validate oceanographic satellites data, to comparer these data to conventional observations and digital models outputs, we have at one's disposal :<P>

<H2>ERS1 and ERS2 data<IMG WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=70 HSPACE=10 VSPACE=10 SRC="images/satellite.jpeg"></H2> 

primary parameter (level 1.5) : instrumental data<P>

<B>Geophysical parameters :</B>

<UL>
<LI>UWI : wind strength and direction, resolution 25km*25km, broke of 500km,
<LI>URA : wind module and H1/3, resolution 6km*6km under track,
<LI>UWA : waves spectrum, one spectrum every 250 km,
<LI>UAT : ATSR, surface water temperature, resolution 25km*25km, broke of 500km.
</UL>

<BR>
<B>CLS/ARGOS data</B><P>

Wind module<P>

Significant height of waves<P>

<HR>
