<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>METEO-FRANCE : Digital forecast</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY>
<H1><CENTER>Digital forecast with ARPEGE model</CENTER></H1>

<HR>

<H2>ARPEGE model</H2>

<I>Digital weather forecast relies, in a large proportion, upon the use of atmosphere digital simulation softwares, usually called "models". M&eacute;t&eacute;o-France has put into operational service, the december 6th 1993, the most advanced version of the new </I><B>ARPEGE</B><I> model.</I>
<P>
<P>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10 SRC="images/arpege.gif">
The ARPEGE main innovation is its variable horizontal resolution : atmosphere is separated into small elemantary "boxes" whose horizontal size is minimal on France, to grow progressively up to antipodes where it is maximal. So we can, with an unique model, make fine-scale forecost on metropolotain territory, while describing with a sufficient description great phenomenons on global scale. 
<P>
ARPEGE model supplies twice a day forecasts with a resolution of <B>20 km for France and 300 km for antipodes</B>.

<BR CLEAR=LEFT><BR>
This new digital tool is developped in close collaboration with ECMWF (European Center of Meteorological Weather Forecast). It is conceived in the beginning as multi-purpose, allowing to make forecasts short-dated (up to three days), or to contribute to study of climate fluctuations and evolution.
<P>

<HR>
<A HREF="index_eng.html"><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE WIDTH=115 HEIGHT=25 HSPACE=5 SRC="images/aviso2.gif">Back to AVISO Home Page</A>
<HR>
<A HREF="http://www.meteo.fr/e_index.html">
<IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE WIDTH=43 HEIGHT=43 SRC="/icons/meteo.gif">
Back to M&eacute;t&eacute;o-France Home Page</A>
<HR SIZE=5>
