<html>
<head>
<title>Ken Gaillot Jr.</title>
</head>
<body>

<h1 align=center>Ken Gaillot Jr.</h1>

<p>Internet electronic mail: <a
href="mailto:scimitar@scimitar.com">scimitar@scimitar.com</a>.</p>

<h2>Education</h2>

<p>Bachelor of Science, December 1991<br>
<a href="http://www.lsu.edu/">Louisiana State University</a>,
Baton Rouge, Louisiana<br>
Major: Computer Science; Minor: Economics</p>

<p>Honors High School Diploma, May 1987<br>
The Holy Cross School, New Orleans, Louisiana</p>

<h2>Experience</h2>

<hr>

<p><a href="http://www.gulf.net/">Gulf Coast Internet Company</a>, 6/95 -
present</p>

<p>As systems team leader for a regional Internet service provider,
I am responsible for system and network administration of a large network
of computer equipment and management of three employees.</p>

<ul>
<li>maintained Unix servers at several company and customer sites in
	various cities in two states
<li>maintained local Ethernet networks running TCP/IP and NetBEUI
<li>maintained large telephone line rotaries for dial-up Internet access
	including channelized T1s and ISDN PRIs
<li>maintained wide area TCP/IP networks including routers,
	modem servers, POTS, ISDN, 56Kbps, switched 56Kpbs,
	fractional and full T1 lines, modems and CSU/DSUs
<li>installed and configured dedicated Internet/intranet servers for routing,
	firewalling, email, DNS and web service
<li>developed and conducted regular series of Internet classes, including
	an introductory Internet seminar and an introductory Web authoring
	seminar
<li>managed Domain Name Service for hundreds of domains
<li>managed IP address space for dozens of Class C networks
<li>wrote custom Perl and C++ programs for various administrative
	and accounting tasks
<li>maintained dozens of virtual World Wide Web servers and assisted
	with authoring content
<li>managed employees handling system and network administration
	including Microsoft Windows'95 and Windows NT administration,
	domain name registration, software installation and configuration,
	and custom programming projects
</ul>

<hr>

<p><a href="index.html">Scimitar Internet Services</a>, 9/94 - present</p>

<p>As Head Honcho of Scimitar, I maintain World Wide Web magazines,
and have on occasion consulted with individuals and businesses on
maximizing the value of their Internet access.</p>

<ul>
<li>responsible for the Web server,
	<a href="http://www.scimitar.com/">www.scimitar.com</a></li>
<li>designed series of courses for Internet usage.</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<p><a href="http://www.harc.edu/">Houston Advanced Research Center</a>,
1/92 - 8/94</p>

<p>At HARC's <a href="http://gtri.harc.edu/">Geotechnology Research
Institute</a>, I supported research personnel through C-language
programming, system planning and system administration.</p>

<ul>
<li>authored C code in heterogeneous networked UNIX environment.
<li>assisted in administration of computer systems and local
Internet-connected TCP/IP network.
<li>designed initial version of GTRI's
	<a href="http://gtri.harc.edu/">World Wide Web pages</a> and server
<li>proposed and implemented $200,000 computer equipment purchase
along with long-term plan to meet computer resource needs.
<li>assisted with major biannual presentations to research
consortium subscribers, including writing reports, running computer
demonstrations and giving talks.
<li>developed software for accessing and processing geophysical
data, including software for visualization, format handling
and device I/O.
<li>wrote visualization software which required use of the
X windows toolkit and OSF/Motif and involved writing a
seismic trace plot widget.
<li>wrote I/O software which required use of TCP/IP networking
and writing device handlers for specialized devices such
as an Exabyte robotics tape carousel and a 3480 cartridge stack-loader.
<li>improved portability, robustness and ease-of-use of programs
originally developed by staff geophysicists.
<li>found, obtained and installed free software from the Internet.
<li>helped with visualization of data from the Magellan probe of
the planet Venus.
</ul>

<hr>

<p>Louisiana State University, 9/87 - 12/91</p>

<p>While a student, I worked part-time as a C programmer for three
LSU research departments: the Southern Region Climate Center, the
Department of Agricultural Engineering and the Remote Sensing and
Image Processing Center.</p>

<ul>
<li>worked as UNIX system programmer, writing applications for
research projects.
<li>helped download and install software from the Internet.
<li>programmed extensively with ELAS remote sensing software,
including writing a display driver to use SunView windows as display devices.
<li>entrusted with root access at each center
</ul>

<hr>

<p><cite>The Wonderland Times</cite>, 4/89 - 12/90</p>

<p>I edited and wrote for the independent student-run monthly magazine.</p>

<ul>
<li>learned desktop publishing and subscriber database management.
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>Computer Languages</h2>

<ul>
<li>Fluent in C, C++, Perl and Bourne/C shell scripting.
<li>Knowledgeable in Fortran, Pascal, SQL, COBOL, Prolog and LISP.
</ul>

<h2>Hardware and Operating Systems</h2>

<ul>
<li><p>Extensive experience in the use and administration of UNIX
workstations, including <a href="http://www.sgi.com/">Silicon Graphics</a>,
<a href="http://www.sun.com/">Sun Microsystems</a>
and Solbourne products, as well as Intel-based PC's running
<a href="http://www.linux.org/">Linux</a> and
<a href="http://www.bsdi.com/">BSD/OS</a>.</p>

<li><p>Extensive experience in the administration of networking hardware
including <a href="http://www.cisco.com/">Cisco</a> routers and modem servers,
<a href="http://www.livingston.com/">Livingston</a> modem servers,
<A href="http://www.xylogics.com/">Xylogics</a> Annex modem servers,
<A href="http://www.ascend.com/">Ascend</a> Max modem/ISDN servers,
<a href="http://www.gandalf.ca/">Gandalf</a> ISDN servers,
<A href="http://www.adtran.com/">Adtran</a> CSU/DSUs,
and various brands of modems.</p>

<li><p>Extensive experience in the use of the NEC SX-3/22 vector
supercomputer.</p>

<li><p>Strong experience in the use and administration of IBM-compatible
PCs running Microsoft DOS, Microsoft Windows, Microsoft Windows'95
and Microsoft Windows NT.</p>

<li><p>Some experience in the use of IBM 3084 mainframe running
VM/CMS, VAX running VMS, Novell Netware and Apple Macintosh computers.</p>
</ul>

<h2>Memberships, Honors and Awards</h2>

<ul>
<li>Member, 1994 - present, <a href="http://www.isoc.org/">Internet Society</a>.
<li>Member, 1994 - present,
	<a href="http://www.toastmasters.org/">Toastmasters</a>.
<li>Newsletter editor, 1993 - 1994, Houston
	<a href="http://www.sgi.com/">Silicon Graphics</a> Users' Group.
<li>County Chair, 1993 - 1994,
	<a href="http://www.lp.org/">Libertarian Party</a>
	of Montgomery County, Texas.
<li>Recipient, 1987, LSU Honor Scholorship.
<li>Recipient, 1987, LSU Alumni Federation Scholarship.
<li>National Merit Scholar, 1987.
</ul>

</body>
