<head>
<title>Scimi-what?</title>
</head>

<body>

<center><img src="nameplate.gif" alt="SCIMITAR Internet Services"></center>

<h1>What is a scimitar?</h1>

<p>A scimitar is a short curved sword once used in the Middle East. I chose the
name for Scimitar Internet Services for no particular reason. It just
sounded good (connotations of speed and power).</p>

<p>A few other uses of the word scimitar:</p>

<ul>

<li><p><a
href="http://vh.radiology.uiowa.edu/GrandRounds/PedsChest/chest.html"><b>Scimitar</b>
syndrome</a> (<i>med.</i>): a pulmonary development anomaly</p>

<li><p>Shakespeare.</p>

<p>From <cite>Troilus and Cressida</cite>, <a
href="http://the-tech.mit.edu/Shakespeare/Comedy/TC/TC.5.1.html">Act 5 Scene
1</a>:</p>

<blockquote>
<p>ACHILLES: I'll heat his blood with Greekish wine to-night,
Which with my <b>scimitar</b> I'll cool to-morrow.
Patroclus, let us feast him to the height.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>From <cite>Titus and Andronicus</cite>, <a
href="http://the-tech.mit.edu/Shakespeare/Tragedy/Titus/Titus.4.2.html">Act 4
Scene 2</a>:</p>

<blockquote>
<p>AARON: Stay, murderous villains! will you kill your brother?
     Now, by the burning tapers of the sky,
     That shone so brightly when this boy was got,
     He dies upon my <b>scimitar's</b> sharp point
     That touches this my first-born son and heir!</p>
</blockquote>

<li><p>a high-performance engineering <a
href="http://csrp.tamu.edu/Soaring/HPE.Scimitar.html">sailplane</a></p>

<li><p>Part of the symbol for the <a
href="gopher://ftp.cac.psu.edu/00/genealogy/roots-l/FAQ.MASON">Shriners</a></p>

<li><p>From <cite>Monty Python and the Holy Grail</cite>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>DENNIS:  Well you can't expect to wield supreme executive power
just 'cause some watery tart threw a sword at you!</p>

<p>ARTHUR:  Shut up!</p>

<p>DENNIS:  I mean, if I went around sayin' I was an emperor just because
some moistened bint had lobbed a <b>scimitar</b> at me they'd put me away!</p>
</blockquote>

<li><p>A model of car from Reliant Motors Ltd. (UK).</p></li>

</ul>

<p>Amazing what you can find on the Web, isn't it?</p>

</body>
</html>
