<head>
<title>Community and Social Issues</title>
</head>
<body>

<center><a href="http://www.gulf.net/">
<img src="/revolution/sponsors/gcic.gif"
alt="Gulf Coast Internet Company"></a></center>

<h1>Community and Social Issues</h1>

<p>Functional, satisfying communities are built by the efforts of
everyone in them to achieve common goals. The trend in the 20th century
to nationalize all social issues takes responsibility away from
local groups, puts control in the hands of people far removed from
the actual problems, and results in a one-size-fits-all approach
that is inappropriate to the great diversity of human community.</p>

<p>Libertarians support having private organizations rather than
government trying to solve social problems.</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="educate/">Education</a></li>
<li><A href="welfare/">Welfare, poverty and entitlements</a></li>
<li><A href="women/">Women's issues</a></li>
<li><A href="race/">Race and ethnicity</a></li>
<li><A href="books/">Books</a></li>
<li><A href="humor/">Humor</a></li>
<li><A href="online/">Online resources</a></li>
<li><A href="quotes/">Quotes</a></li>
</ul>

