</DOCHDR>
<html>

<head>
<title>Politics</title>
</head>

<body>

<center><a href="http://www.scimitar.com/">
<img src="/revolution/sponsors/scimitar.gif"
alt="SCIMITAR Internet Services"></a></center>

<h1>Politics</h1>

<p>Ah, politics. That's what we're here for, isn't it? Perhaps
the reason libertarians have had such limited success politically
is that most libertarians would rather do <em>anything</em>
other than politics.</p>

<h2><a href="lpus/">The Libertarian Party</a></h2>
<h2><a href="strategy/">Strategy Tips for Libertarian Activists</a></h2>

<ul>
<li><P>Political organizations
	<ul>
	<li><a href="cato.html">The Cato Institute</a></li>
	<li><a href="napm.html">The Not A Penny More Campaign</a></li>
	<li><A href="actnz.html">ACT New Zealand</a></li>
	<li><a href="/revolution/by_name/B/BLF.html">Buckeye Liberty
		Foundation</a></li>
	<li><img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
		href="http://www.pond.com/~famularo/">Libertarian
		Forum of Delaware Valley</a></li>
	<li><a href="orgs.html">Other libertarian organizations</a></li>
	</ul></p>
<li><P>Political history
	<ul>
	<li><a href="/revolution/philosophy/libertarian.html">What's
		in a name?</a>: choosing the word libertarian</li>
	<li><a href="thirdp.html">Minor parties in the U.S.</a>
	<li><a href="magarts.html">A Libertarian chronology:
		magazine articles 1972 - 1986</a></li>
	</ul></p>
<li><P>Issue politics
	<ul>
	<li><a href="/revolution/firearms/politics/">Firearms politics</a></li>
	</ul></p>
<li><a href="products.html">Libertarian-interest products</a>
<li><a href="famous.html">Famous libertarians</a>
