<head>
<title>About Revolution</title>
</head>
<body>

<h1>About Revolution</h1>

<p><a href="/revolution/"><b>Revolution</b></a> provides
<font size=+1>intellectual ammunition</font>
to everyone fighting for more freedom around the
<A href="/revolution/by_place/">world</a> -- the peaceful revolution
of ideas and technology. Revolution is
a <a href="search.html">searchable</a> collection of facts, arguments
and statistics furthering the libertarian
idea of individuals freely collaborating in society.</p>

<p>I (<a href="/revolution/by_name/G/KenGaillotJr.html">Ken Gaillot</a>)
maintain this site in my spare time, which unfortunately is not very
abundant. As a result, I do not get to add all the information I would
like, and I do not get to respond to all the email I receive. I do read
every suggestion and try to incorporate them into the site.</p>

<p>If you have comments, corrections or information
you wish to be added, fill out the <a href="comments.html">comment form</a>
or send e-mail to <img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
href="mailto:scimitar@scimitar.com">scimitar@scimitar.com</a>.</p>

<p><a href="sponsors/">Sponsorship</a> is available.</p>

<hr>

<h2>What those little pictures mean</h2>

<p>To distinguish links that go to other <b>Revolution</b> pages from links
that go off yonder in to the net, the following markers are used for external
references.</p>

<ul>
<li><img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]">Web site
<li><img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]">E-mail address
<li><img src="/images/gopher.gif" alt="[GOPHER]">Gopher site
<li><img src="/images/ftp.gif" alt="[FTP]">FTP site
<li><img src="/images/news.gif" alt="[USENET]">Usenet news group
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>Credits</h2>

<p>The flag images used in the <a href="/revolution/by_place/">by place</a>
area are copyright <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.adfa.oz.au/CS/flags/">Christopher Vance</a>. Used with
permission.</p>

<p>The maps used in the <a href="/revolution/by_place/">by place</a> area
are public-domain images from <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://wings.buffalo.edu/world/">The Virtual Tourist</a>.</p>

<p>The Internet icons are slight variations of public-domain images from
<img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.cit.gu.edu.au/~anthony/icons/index.html">Anthony's Icon
Library</a>.</p>

<p>Revolution's <a href="search.html">search engine</a> is
<img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a href="http://www.excite.com/">Excite
for Web Servers</a>.</p>

<p>Information in Revolution was collected from Internet
mailing lists, news groups, FTP sites and World-Wide Web sites, as well as more
traditional sources such as newspapers, magazines and books. Revolution's
newspaper of record is the
<a href="/revolution/by_name/N/NandO.html">NandO Times</a>.</p>

<hr>

