<head>
<title>Contacting the Davidians</title>
<!-- Place: Three Rivers, Texas (USA); El Reno, Oklahoma (USA);
	Oakdale, Louisiana (USA); Anthony, New Mexico (USA);
	Danbury, Connecticut (USA) -->
<!-- Time: incarcerated June 1994, each 5 - 30 years -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>Contacting the Davidians</h1>

<p>The Branch Davidian prisoners' addresses are listed below. Some
have been transferred several times, so the addresses may not be
up to date. (F.C.I. = Federal Correctional Institution.)</p>

<ul>
<li>Kevin Whitecliff, #60537-080, F.C.I.--Box 4200,
Three Rivers, Texas 78071

<li>Brad Branch, #60536-080, F.C.I.--Box 4200,
Three Rivers, Texas 78071

<li>Renos Avraam, #60590-080, F.C.I., 2680 Highway 301 South,
Gesup, Georgia 31599</li>

<li>Jaime Castillo, #60594-080, F.C.I.--Box 5000,
Oakdale, Louisiana 71463

<li>Paul Fatta, #61154-079, F.C.I.--Box 3000,
Anthony, New Mexico 88021

<li>Ruth Riddle, #60596-080, F.C.I.--33 1/2 Pembroke Rd.,
Danbury, Connecticut 06811

<li>Graeme Craddock, #60593-080, F.C.I.--Box 5000,
Oakdale, Louisiana 71463

<li>Livingston Fagan, #60550-080, F.C.I.,
Leavenworth, Kansas</li>
</ul>

<p>Small contributions for the prisoners' postage and
telephone needs can be made directly to the prisoners (a
postal or western union money order with their name and I.D. number).</p>

<p>Or make contributions, including larger ones, to
surviving Branch Davidians in Waco, earmarking them for the
prisoners or for the general fund:</p>

<p>Mount Carmel Survivors Memorial Fund Inc., Box 120, Axtell, TX 76624.</p>

<p>The Mount Carmel Memorial is located at Double EE Ranch Road off Highway
2491, east of Waco,
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/tx/">Texas</a>.</p>

