<head>
<title>Forbes Health Insurance Plan</title>
<!-- Place: USA -->
<!-- Time: report 1994 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>Forbes' Health Insurance Alternative</h1>

<p>August 1994, from <a href="/revolution/by_name/H/TFranklinHarrisJr.html">T.
Franklin Harris Jr.</a>, Critic-at-Large, <cite>The Exchange: Culture Reason
Style</cite>:</p>

<p>The Forbes plan gives cash bonuses to employees who do not file health
insurance claims -- that is, to employees to economize, shop 
around, and pay out of pocket for non-catastrophic or routine health care. 
Forbes has saved enough on insurance to more than pay for the bonuses 
they offer. Meanwhile, employees have very high marks for their company's
system.</p>

