<head>
<title>U.S. Postal Service</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>The U.S. Mail Monopoly</h1>

<p>Of all the ridiculous ideas thought up by advocates of big government,
one of the worst has got to be the idea that the U.S. federal government
should deliver all the mail in the entire country. What advantage does
government have in delivering mail? They keep costs down so well? They're
so in tune with the customer? I don't get it. Government is there, essentially,
to kill people or lock them up. That's what it's good at. Delivering the mail
is best left to private companies.</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="express.html">USPS harasses express mail users</a></li>
</ul>

