<head>
<title>Internet Offends Malaysia</title>
<!-- Place: Malaysia -->
<!-- Time: 1990's -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>Malaysia Offended by Internet</h1>

<p>The <a href="/revolution/by_place/Asia/Malaysia/">Malaysian</a> government
is offended that people are criticizing
Malaysia on the Internet. Information Minister (what an Orwellian title)
Mohamed Rahmat condemned the dissent, saying that Malaysian students abroad
are smearing the country's good name and the government is considering
laws to curb such "abuses." Rahmat suggested that people seeking information
about Malaysia read officially sanctioned sources such as <cite>The Star</cite>
and <cite>Berita Harian</cite> newspapers.</p>

<p>Awww, we're sorry, we never meant to offend any anal bureaucrats in some
country that can't tell its information policy from a hole
in the ground. <b>Revolution</b> extends a hearty welcome to all Malaysians
who have disobeyed their government and read this page!</p>

<hr>

<p>Source: Reuter Information Service article "Minister says students
smear Malaysia on Internet," reprinted in the September 11, 1995 <cite>News
and Observer</cite>.</p>

