<head>
<title>Violence Already Illegal</title>
<!-- Place: Washington, DC (USA) -->
<!-- Time: testimony March 31, 1995 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>Bad Guys' Gun Usage Already Illegal</h1>

<p>From the <a href="index.html">March 31, 1995 statement</a> of Tulane
University criminologist James Wright before the U.S. House of Representatives
Subcommittee on Crime of the Committee on the Judiciary:</p>

<p>My seventh observation is that everything the bad guys do with
their guns is already against the law.  That criminals will
generally be indifferent to the law would seem to follow from the
definition of the terms, but it's a lesson that we've had to learn
time and again throughout our history.  As a matter of fact, and as
has already been stated by the panel this morning, gun acquisition
by felons, whether from retail or private sources, for whatever
reason, is already_illegal. Yet obviously felons still acquire
guns.  Since practically everything the bad guys do with their guns,
or do to obtain their guns is already against the law, one is
entitled to wonder whether there is some new law that we haven't
yet thought up that we can somehow pass that will persuade them to
stop it.</p>

<hr><p align=center><font size=-1 color="#990000">
