<head>
<title>Ancients on Self-Defense</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Ancients on Self-Defense</h1>

<hr>

<h2>Seneca the Younger on Responsibility</h2>

<p>A sword never kills anybody; it is a tool in the killer's hand.</p>

<p>-- Lucius Annaeus Seneca, c. 4BC - 65AD.</p>

<hr>

<h2>Jesus on Self-Defense</h2>

<p>He that hath no sword, let him sell his garment and buy one.</p>

<p>-- the Bible, Luke 22:36.</p>

<hr><p align=center><font size=-1 color="#990000">
