<head>
<title>Cryptography</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Cryptography</h1>

<p>Cryptography is the art of making and breaking codes. Crypto is
at the center of electronic privacy, being able to communicate privately
with whom you choose -- and keeping everyone else, including
government agents, from listening in.</p>

<p>The United States considers encryption technology a munition,
putting it under the same export controls used for nuclear weapons.
Ironically, the computer source code for an encryption algorithm can
be exported outside the United States without controls, but an
electronic copy of the same code is restricted.</p>

<p>Topics in crypto:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="pgp/">Pretty Good Privacy</a>: protection for the masses
<li><a href="escrow/">Key escrow</a>: encryption with built-in
	wiretap, including the notorious Clipper Chip</a>
<li><A href="bernstein.html">Export controls ruled unconstitutional</a></li>
</ul>

