<head>
<title>George Washington</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>George Washington</h1>

<p>George Washington, American Revolutionary, Founding Father, was the first
President of the United States.</p>

<p>Libertarians respect Washington for the role he played in American
independence, but Washington seemed more concerned with
social order than with liberty. Thinkers like <a
href="/revolution/by_name/J/ThomasJefferson.html">Thomas Jefferson</a> and
<a href="/revolution/by_name/P/ThomasPaine.html">Thomas Paine</a> are closer
to current libertarian thought. (Of course this is in
relative terms; Washington would be infinitely preferable to any of the
scumbags the Presidency has seen lately.)</p>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/firearms/quotes/founders.html">
	Founding Fathers' quotes on firearms</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/multi/war/quotes.html">
	Quotes on war</a></li>
</ul>

