<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/va/">VA</a> 22030.</p>

<p>From the March 25, 1994 Everett, Washington <cite>The Herald</cite>:</p>

<p>In what is becoming a trend on the west coast, John Ayler was
forced to shoot a cougar that charged him and a friend.  Noticing
his dogs were acting oddly, Ayler, of
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/wa/Arlington.html">Arlington</a>,
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/wa/">Washington</a>, put his
gun in his belt, and with his friend went outside to look around.
When, instead of fleeing, the cougar charged directly at the two men, Ayler
pulled his gun and killed the cat.</p>

