<head>
<title>Bosnia</title>
<!-- Place: Bosnia -->
<!-- Time: 1990's -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>Bosnia</h1>

<P>Okay, let's see, the Balkans are called "the tinderbox of <a
href="/revolution/by_place/Europe/">Europe</a>" for
its residents' tendency to kill each other, let's get the
world's superpowers involved in a conflict there.</p>

<p>Serbs, Croats and Muslims have been fighting each other in the Balkans
for hundreds of years. With the collapse of Yugoslavia, they began pouncing
on each other once again. NATO, the U.N. and other nincompoops felt a moral
obligation to get themselves killed as well.</p>

<p>One of the many complications in all this is that the
<a href="/revolution/by_place/Asia/Russia/">Russians</a> have been ethnic
allies of the Serbs for hundreds of years, and don't take kindly to Western
nations' intervention on behalf of Croats and Muslims.</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="srebrenica.html">July 1995: Serbs conquer Srebrenica, massacre
	Muslims</a></li>
<li><a href="yeltsin.html">September 1995: Russians threaten European
	war</a></li>
<li><a href="ilidza.html">March 1996: Muslims loot Serb homes
	after regaining Sarajevo</a></li>
</ul>

