<head>
<title>Health Care</title>
</head>
<body>

<h1>Health Care</h1>

<p>Health care is an intimate issue of freedom. Governments today preempt many
health care decisions, such as what drugs you can choose from, who can be your
doctor and what type of insurance you can have.</p>

<p>Contents:</p>
<ul>
<li>Health insurance and alternatives
	<ul>
	<li><a href="cbn.html">Christian group funds health care</a>
	<li><a href="insurance.html">The insurance industry</a>
	<li><a href="medicare.html">Medicare</a>
	<li><a href="forbes.html">Forbes rewards employee cost savings</a>
	</ul>
<li>Government-run health care
	<ul>
	<li><a href="britain.html">The British system</a>
	<li><a href="canada.html">The Canadian system</a>
	<li><a href="immunize.html">Clinton's child immunization proposal</a>
	<li><a href="clinton.html">Criticism of Clinton's health care plan</a>
	</ul>
<li>Drugs, vitamins and supplements
	<ul>
	<li><a href="supplem.html">Health supplements</a>
	<li><a href="fda.html">The Food and Drug Administration</a>
	<li><a href="/revolution/body/drugs/">Drug prohibition</a>
	</ul>
<li><a href="lp_phc.html">The Libertarian Party's Project Healthy
	Choice</a></li>
<li><a href="fallacy.html">Fallacies of the health care debate</a></li>
<li><a href="books/">Books</a></li>
</ul>

