<head>
<title>Books on Self-Ownership</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Books on Self-Ownership</h1>

<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/body/drugs/books/">Drugs</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/body/health/books/">Health care</a></li>
</ul>

<hr>
<h2><cite>Ain't Nobody's Business If You Do</cite></h2>

<p><a href="/revolution/by_name/M/PeterMcWilliams.html">Peter McWilliams</a>
has written a masterful book exposing the follies of prohibition for
what they are. <cite>Ain't Nobody's Business If You Do: The Absurdity of
Consensual Crimes in a Free Society</cite> "marshals a vast army of anecdotes,
quotes, statistics and assertions to argue that America would be a lot
better off if we stopped using the force of law to save each other from
drugs, alcohol, gambling, pornography, suicide and sex in its more exotic
flavors," according to the New York <cite>Times</cite>.</p>

<p>The book is fun to read and even browse, as compelling and/or witty
quotes are scattered about everywhere.</p>

<p>McWilliams, in the spirit of creativity unleashed, has put the
entire contents of <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.mcwilliams.com/books/aint/f01.htm"><cite>Nobody's
Business</cite></a> online. Highly recommended.</p>

