<head>
<title>Canadian Health Care System</title>
<!-- Place: Canada -->
<!-- Time: report 1994 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>The Canadian Health Care System</h1>

<p>I've lost the author and date of this report on
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/Canada/">Canada's</a>
national health care system:</p>

<p>In a recent <cite>Wall Street Journal</cite>, a woman described the
horrors of childbirth, without anesthesia -- yet another cutback in Ontario.
Anesthesiologists are becoming rare in the smaller cities, and
now available only during "business hours" even in Toronto.
If you have a baby at night in Toronto -- or in a small town --
be prepared to scream a lot.</p>

<p>The government had announced cancellation of of any epidural
reimbursements in Thunder Bay.</p>

<p>The article did mention that Ontario anethesiologists get only
$100, but failed to observe that this was the likely cause of
the shortage of these <em>specialists</em> in Ontario.</p>

<p>And, it's not just the rich who come to the U.S. for treatment.
Last month's <em>Readers Digest</em> described a retired blue-collar worker
who was forced to sell his house and liquidate his savings, because
he was "too old" to receive a bone marrow transplant in Ontario.</p>

